Private Banks Are Still Struggling to Attract Clients, FT Says

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-07-13T04:59:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/private-banks-are-still-struggling-to-attract-clients-ft-says.html
Private banks throughout the world
are still finding difficulty attracting new clients in the wake
of the financial crisis, according to a study published today by
Scorpio Partnership, a firm of wealth-management consultants,
the Financial Times reported.  New money paid into private banks declined by almost 19
percent last year, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 